       Protests


       The Vehicle Code grants the Board jurisdiction to decide cases
       involving:
         * Vehicle Code § 3060, et seq.
           Attempts by a franchisor to:

         * terminate/refuse to continue (renew)
         * modify the franchise

         Vehicle Code § 3062(a)(1)

   Attempts by the franchisor to:
     * establish a new dealership

     Vehicle Code § 3062(a)(2)

   Attempts by the franchisor to:
     * establish a satellite warranty facility
     * relocate an existing satellite warranty facility

     Vehicle Code § 3064

   Disputes relating to the dealer's:
     * delivery and preparation obligations, and compensation for such
       services

     Vehicle Code § 3065

   Disputes relating to:
     * reimbursement for warranty work

     Vehicle Code § 3065.1

   Disputes relating to:
     * reimbursement for franchisor incentive programs


